storage.description:
Where outputs land. Common shapes:
  {service: "s3", region, bucket, credentials: {access_key_id, secret_access_key}}
  {service: "gcs", bucket, credentials: {...}}
  {service: "do" | "backblaze" | "rackspace" | "linode" | "upcloud" | "wasabi" | ...}
  {service: "ftp", host, user, password}
By default Coconut uploads to your own storage; without a storage block, files stay in Coconut for ~24h.
